					<![CDATA[
						 <p>In E. F. Benson's book, &quot;The Freaks of Mayfair&quot;, there's a reference to a singing teacher of such skill that he could 'turn a corncrake into a contralto'.</p> <p>Dr. Spanko is the only other fictional mention of corncrakes I have encountered. Coincidence? Almost certainly!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
